%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%% Hand 26 
st||RH||ah|Raises in Competition|ah|When the bidding is 1C-1S|ah|Hand  26|md|3s76 HT865 CAQT75 D96,,,|sv||mb|1c1s?|NT|^B@2
You are sitting South and the bidding is as shown above.|
pg| ***** 39 ***** |


NT||lb|*bWhat would you bid?^^3c|mb|3c|nt|
^b@2Here the choice is not as clear. Most people would double and that might work out when partner has a strong hand and hearts. But remember you only have an 8-card fit at best in hearts (partner would open 1H with 5) and they probably have a spade fit. So tactically I like 3C better. |
PG| ***** 41 ***** |


NT|^B@2
It makes it harder for them to bid in spades and you are likely to have a 9-card fit. At least partner will probably be better positioned to compete when you bid 3C. Therefore, despite my 4 hearts, I recommend 3C (but if you want to double, that could work out on some hands).|
