%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%% Hand 27 
st||RH||ah|Raises in Competition|ah|When the bidding is 1C-1S|ah|Hand  27|md|3SA876 HT8 CAQT8 D964,,,|sv||mb|1c1s?|NT|^B@2
You are sitting South and the bidding is as shown above.|
pg| ***** 43 ***** |


NT||lb|*bWhat would you bid?^^1n|mb|1n|nt|
^b@2Both 2S and 1N are possible. 2S identifies your strong clubs. It also is more preemptive, always good in competition. On the other hand 1N shows your points, spade stopper, and is more precise. I would lean towards 1N, unless playing against a real strong pair, where I want to get in their way with 2S. Either is fine.|
